Mellanox Technologies, Teva and Strauss: Israel Equity Preview

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-09-21T06:24:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/mellanox-technologies-teva-and-strauss-israel-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
the company names, and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index gained 3.3 percent to 1,067.99 in Tel Aviv.  Mellanox Technologies Ltd. (MLNX)  : The adapter maker
priced an offering of 3 million shares at $31.75, the equivalent
of 116.78 shekels, each. Mellanox lost 0.9 percent to 125
shekels.  Strauss Group Ltd. (STRS)  :  Israel ’s second-largest food
producer is in talks to sell all or part of its overseas coffee
activities to  Sara Lee Corp. (SLE) , TheMarker reported, without saying
where it got the information. Strauss rose 4.1 percent to 42.69
shekels.  Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA)  : The world’s
largest maker of generic drugs is “very confident” it can get
its version of Sanofi’s Lovenox approved, William Marth,
president and chief executive officer of Teva Pharmaceutical
Americas, said. Teva dropped 1.4 percent to 138.30 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in  Tel Aviv  at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  